From: Md Arif <111168803+sabamdarif@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] disable Bionic heap pointer tagging at process start

On Android 11+ (arm64) Bionic's allocator returns heap pointers with a
tag in the top byte (0xb4...), so bit 63 is always set. LibreOffice
round-trips raw pointers through decimal strings in several places and
parses them back with signed toInt64 (rtl_str_toInt64_WithLength clamps
values above INT64_MAX to 0):

  - vcl/unx/gtk3/gtksalmenu.cxx: GtkSalMenu* encoded into GAction
    names; the clamped parse returned null and the first click on any
    menubar entry crashed in GtkSalMenu::Activate (SIGSEGV at the
    mpVCLMenu load, verified on device).
  - sw/source/core/fields/cellfml.cxx: SwTableBox* in Writer table
    formulas (8 sites).
  - sw/source/uibase/misc/redlndlg.cxx, svx/source/dialog/
    docrecovery.cxx: pointers in tree-view row ids.

Rather than patching each site, disable heap tagging for the whole
process before anything is allocated, the same workaround Termux
applies to qemu and openjdk:
https://github.com/termux/termux-packages/blob/ec0fa2f/packages/qemu-system-x86-64-headless/0016-Add-workaround-for-tagged-pointers-on-Android-12.patch

sal_detail_initialize is run first by every SAL_IMPLEMENT_MAIN binary
(soffice.bin, unopkg, ...), so hooking it covers them all. mallopt is
resolved via dlsym because the M_BIONIC_SET_HEAP_TAGGING_LEVEL
interface only exists on Bionic (API 31+); on older API levels the
android_mallopt fallback is used. Only allocations made after the call
are untagged, hence the placement at the very top, before the
InitializeSoffice early return.
---

--- a/sal/osl/unx/salinit.cxx
+++ b/sal/osl/unx/salinit.cxx
@@ -42,9 +42,45 @@
 #include <syslog.h>
 #endif
 
+#ifdef __TERMUX__
+#include <dlfcn.h>
+#include <android/api-level.h>
+
+#ifndef M_BIONIC_SET_HEAP_TAGGING_LEVEL
+#define M_BIONIC_SET_HEAP_TAGGING_LEVEL (-204)
+#endif
+
+// Bionic tags heap pointers in the top byte (0xb4...), which breaks the
+// signed toInt64 round-trips LibreOffice uses to pass raw pointers through
+// strings (gtksalmenu.cxx GAction names, cellfml.cxx table formulas,
+// tree-view row ids). Turn tagging off for the whole process before any
+// such pointer can be allocated.
+static void android_disable_heap_tagging() {
+    void* lib_handle = dlopen("libc.so", RTLD_LAZY);
+    if (!lib_handle)
+        return;
+    if (android_get_device_api_level() >= 31) {
+        auto mallopt_func
+            = reinterpret_cast<int (*)(int, int)>(dlsym(lib_handle, "mallopt"));
+        if (mallopt_func)
+            mallopt_func(M_BIONIC_SET_HEAP_TAGGING_LEVEL, 0);
+        return;
+    }
+    auto android_mallopt = reinterpret_cast<bool (*)(int, void*, size_t)>(
+        dlsym(lib_handle, "android_mallopt"));
+    if (android_mallopt) {
+        int tag_level = 0;
+        android_mallopt(8, &tag_level, sizeof(tag_level));
+    }
+}
+#endif
+
 extern "C" {
 
 void sal_detail_initialize(int argc, char ** argv) {
+#ifdef __TERMUX__
+    android_disable_heap_tagging();
+#endif
     if (argc == sal::detail::InitializeSoffice)
     {
         sal::detail::setSoffice();
